survey_feedback: This was a very fun survey. I liked thinking about hobbies as I find myself not doing them lately. I have actually been working two jobs since 2020, and it's hard, but I hope I can finally find a job in hr and training that pays enough to not need two jobs. The cost of living skyrocketed because of covid, and I couldn't buy a home when I moved here as I came for grad school. However, recently, I have changed my outlook on life and really want to value my current life and youth. I want to get healthier and not necessarily save money once my bills are paid as I met up with a friend in Japan last year who became paralyzed due to a side effect in the covid vaccine, and she can't work anymore - so I understand the importance in enjoying life now. My other friend was lucky as she got a heart transplant before covid shut everything down, but these people are even younger than me and had these scary experiences, so I value life more now.
